        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Andreas Dilger",
          "email": "andreas.dilger@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-04-29 22:40:25.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-8042 osd-zfs: set ashift=12 recordsize=1024k by default",
        "message": "LU-8042 osd-zfs: set ashift=12 recordsize=1024k by default\n\nWhen creating new OST zpools add the \"ashift=12\" option by default,\nsince it is typical that the underlying storage is using 4KB sectors.\nWithout this parameter, significant performance problems can be seen\non drives that emulate 512-byte sectors, and it may cause problems\nreplacing drives in the future if not specified at format time.\n\nSet the recordsize=1024k option by default for ZFS OSTs to allow ZFS\nblocksize up to 1MB to improve performance for most OST workloads.\nThis can be overridden by \"mkfs.lustre --mkfsoptions=recordsize=128k\"\nat format time, or by \"zfs inherit recordsize <filesystem>\" to clear\nit after the filesystem was formatted.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I540524f67dc467d76695483d0e3bf94d7d3ebbe5\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
